description:
&lt;p&gt;Ystwyth Ward is an 18 bedded acute medical ward containing the hyper acute stroke unit in the beautiful university town of Aberystwyth in west Wales. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We provide direct thrombolysis via CT for patients experiencing stroke symptoms with rapid admission to a dedicated Hyper Acute Stroke Unit located within Ystwyth Ward. Here our patients are treated and monitored for 72 hours while beginning their rehabilitation program under the care of our highly skilled Multi Disciplinary Team.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We have an active involvement in research (national and international, clinical and nurse led) and possibly the best view of any hospital in the country. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for motivated staff nurses to join our team. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Come and work with us to develop your acute nursing skills. Working on Ystwyth Ward will give you scope for development of skills in the rapidly advancing fields of stroke, stroke rehabilitation and acute general medicine. All members of the team are making a difference to the lives of our patients. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Ystwyth Ward provides a great team working experience where staff are valued and supported to develop skills and knowledge in this field of nursing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
